Members of the Professional Golf Association of Nigeria (PGAN) have commended Governor Seriake Dickson for the commissioning 18 Hole worldclass championship golf course built at the reclaimed/sand filled land behind the Government House. Dickson said the commissioning of the golf course which was built by Total Golf Construction of Vero Beach Florida, USA, the same company that built the golf course at Ilara- Mokin, Ondo State was a fulfillment of the promise he made upon assumption of office to turn Bayelsa into tourism hub in the Niger Delta region. According to him as governor he did not have all the answers and solutions to all problems but his ability to recognize talents and people that can deliver made the difference which the construction of the golf course represents. He expressed optimism that the government that would succeed him would key into his dreams and forge ahead with the continued maintenance and development of the golf course. The life President of the PGAN, Major- General IBM Haruna (rtd) said golfers all the country are happy with the initiative which Dickson has brought into fruition. According to him, thr golf course is a money spinner which the state government would not regret building. “We praise you for the initiative, for the vision and pray that those that would succeed you would see the long term vision and wisdom in initiating this golf course and the property that would be developed around it. This is a money spinner.  In the long term it would make more returns that you would get in the stock exchange. 